The article discusses the commitment of APEC leaders to protect the environment. The United States has made protecting the environment a top priority, taking substantial steps such as reducing carbon pollution, protecting sensitive ecosystems, and supporting the development of new technologies. APEC plays a role in promoting green and sustainable growth in the region, focusing on areas like wildlife trafficking, illegal logging, ocean conservation, sustainable mining, chemical health and safety, electric vehicles, and trade in environmental goods. The article also mentions the United States' efforts to combat wildlife trafficking, illegal logging, and illegal fishing, as well as its work on chemical health and safety regulations and promoting the usage of electric vehicles. The United States has led efforts to reduce tariffs on environmental goods and is working on reducing aviation emissions.